body:
Ok, so I keep seeing stuff like this and thinking

1. Maria Hill is dust

2. Hell yeah it’s probably Tony’s funeral, because as far as everyone knows? He hella dead. Half the population died, Tony was on the Big Death Ship, and I’m gonna guess he’s not answering his phone. So yeah, its probably his funeral, but is he really dead? Nah

3. Tony will probably die though but I just thought I should contribute

Avengers: Annihilation script leaked

XXX ENDING SPOILERS AHEAD XXX

Thanos sucks up all the dust from the dead ½ of the universe into his ass and kills himself so the avengers can revive them.

Steve Rogers laughs himself to death because he’s never seen a reverse fart before (idiot), ergo Chris Evans’ emotional goodbye tweets.

Captain marvel punches the the corpse (of Thanos, you moron) and he becomes an old lady who then gives giant dead old lady birth back to Tom holland (the actor) who is then forced at gunpoint by Tony stark to assume the identity of Peter parker to avoid the cosmic wrath of aunt may.

Rocket raccoon strait eats ant man in the end credits sequence. The camera then rotates to reveal the entire cast of parks and recreation, who are now assumed to be the new guardians of the galaxy.

I can see why they’re doing re-shoots. A lot of this shit just makes no fucking sense.

summary: Infinity War: My explanation on the ending
body:
Infinity War: My explanation on the ending

So the majority of us has seen the Marvel’s Infinity War right? (If not do not read beyond this point if you don’t want to be spoiled.) I just finished my second time watching it and I thought of this crazy thing.

As we all know, The majority of Marvel’s star characters had been killed off in the end and some are still alive. I happen to take a notice of a small fact on each dead character shares.

Most of the dead characters had lost at least a loved one, either in their own movies or in a comic. If your confused on what I mean, here’s an example.

Spiderman lost his grandfather. Star-Lord lost his mother, father and Gamora(?). Groot lost Gamora(?). Drax lost his family and Black Panther lost his dad. I don’t know about Doctor Strange or the guy at the very end, how sent a red code to Captain Marvel(?) But I can see some sort of connection.

Thanos lost Gamora and was and still is mourning over her death(?) Maybe to show ‘mercy’ to people like Peter, he allowed them to pass on to the afterlife or something.

This was a random thought in my head as I watched the ending so it’s probably an inaccurate thing XD

title: Random Avenger!Reader Headcanons
body:
Late night thoughts I had when I should’ve been doing homework.

  • You’re basically a manager for them.
  • Every morning you cook breakfast, something specific for them. Steve gets pancakes that are cooked to look like his shield with a side of blueberries and strawberries, Tony gets black coffee only, Bruce gets some cream cheese bagels, Stephen gets eggs benedict, Peter gets web-shaped waffles, Thor gets some jam on rye bread surprisingly, etc.
  • Helping out on missions isn’t difficult because you’re weak, it’s because you’re treated like you’re weak even though you’ve lifted a goddamn Coca-Cola truck before.
  • Cap has actually asked you to help stitch up his teddy bear which has the same armor as him, even a little shield and helmet. Only you know he has this.
  • Peter keeps spilling juice on his web-shooters and you always have to clean the mess.
  • The press is always asking if you have an affair with one of the Avengers or if you like any of them to which you respond, “Any relationship I have with them is merely professional. If anything, I’m their babysitter.” Which only makes them question more.
  • Did I mention that you’re actually more of a babysitter instead?
  • You’ve had to read whole articles, books, and wikis just to understand quantum realms and nanotechnology so you actually know what the hell the smart-asses are saying.
  • Natasha pities you along with Wanda, and they help every now and then, having a girl’s night out.
  • Nick sometimes joins you on the girl’s night out.
  • You might’ve read fanfiction on yourself and other Avengers being shipped with the readers just to get a laugh. Sometimes an Avenger will join you.
  • Whenever you see a fan get so hyped or emotional around you, you just want to shower them with appreciation.
  • There’s fan-made stuff, cosplays, and merch of you and you secretly buy them along with other Avengers merch, hiding them in a secret room as a shrine.
  • You pranked Tony and Sam once by getting JARVIS or FRIDAY to spray-paint their suits highlighter pink, adding smiley-face stickers for nipples on Tony’s suit and puppy stickers on Sam’s wings.
  • They got revenge by hacking into your search history and using it as blackmail.
  • Natasha beat their asses and saved yours.
  • Peter asks what’s going on and you just tell him, “The adults are busy sweetheart, why don’t you go play with your new Millennium Falcon Lego set I bought you in the mail?” He quickly disappears.
  • Stephen, Thor, and Bruce stand there awkwardly watching.
  • Despite all the stupid shit they pull, they’re still the best family ever. And you’re the best babysitter ever. They even got you a mug for that.
